00:53.234 --> 00:54.468
Never thought I'd see

00:54.470 --> 00:56.036
the great Harvey Specter
break a sweat.

00:56.038 --> 00:57.404
You want to race,
Jeffrey?

00:57.406 --> 00:58.939
I'm more than happy
to kick your ass.

00:58.941 --> 01:00.474
Believe me, Harvey,

01:00.476 --> 01:02.209
I didn't get up
at 5:00 a.m. for my health.

01:02.211 --> 01:04.444
A guy like you
in Central Park at this hour?

01:04.447 --> 01:06.847
That's not where
my mind went either.

01:06.849 --> 01:09.483
Only guy I'm here
to solicit is you, buddy.

01:09.485 --> 01:11.518
I'll assume you've heard
of Marco Mendoza.

01:11.520 --> 01:12.753
Yeah, the 16-year-old
tennis phenom.

01:12.755 --> 01:14.321
What about him?

01:14.323 --> 01:16.256
I'm on the cusp
of signing that kid.

01:16.258 --> 01:17.491
I want you
to be part of the team.

01:17.493 --> 01:18.892
Just because
I know about tennis

01:18.894 --> 01:20.360
doesn't mean I
give a shit about tennis.

01:20.362 --> 01:21.862
Hey, the basketballs
in your office

01:21.864 --> 01:23.197
didn't autograph
themselves, Harvey.

01:23.199 --> 01:25.299
You owe me.
Oh, please.

01:25.301 --> 01:27.534
I've brought you just as
many clients as you brought me.

01:27.536 --> 01:30.237
Five minutes with the kid.
That's all I'm asking.

01:30.239 --> 01:33.507
You're an agent, Jeffrey.
It's never all you're asking.

01:33.509 --> 01:38.045
There might be
one slight wrinkle.

01:40.715 --> 01:43.083
So you want me to emancipate
him from his father?

01:43.085 --> 01:45.352
That's a hell of a thing to do
just for a commission.

01:45.354 --> 01:47.321
Just listen
to what he has to say.

01:47.323 --> 01:50.357
Marco, tell him your story.

01:50.359 --> 01:53.060
Look, I've been playing tennis
since before I could walk.

01:53.062 --> 01:55.229
When I was six, I was
crushing kids in high school.

01:55.231 --> 01:56.997
I don't play cards,
I don't drink.

01:56.999 --> 01:59.900
What I do is win.

01:59.902 --> 02:01.535
I like this kid.

02:01.537 --> 02:04.371
So what does that have
to do with your father?

02:04.373 --> 02:06.874
He won't let me go pro.

02:06.876 --> 02:08.241
So it's all
about the money.

02:08.244 --> 02:09.175
No, I don't care
about the money.

02:09.178 --> 02:10.610
You can keep the money.

02:10.613 --> 02:13.514
Nine out of ten tournaments
are closed to amateurs.

02:13.516 --> 02:16.083
If I don't go pro,
I can't play against the best.

02:16.085 --> 02:17.451
And if I can't
play against the best,

02:17.453 --> 02:18.919
I can't be the best.

02:18.921 --> 02:21.755
That's a great speech,
but you're 16,

02:21.757 --> 02:24.992
and what I'm not hearing is why
you can't wait two more years.

02:24.994 --> 02:27.261
People hit their prime
at different ages, Mr. Specter.

02:27.263 --> 02:29.463
Look at me.

02:29.465 --> 02:33.467
I have a chance to be great,
and I have a chance now.

02:51.386 --> 02:52.719
You know that paper doesn't...

02:52.721 --> 02:54.454
put itself
in the machine, right?

02:54.456 --> 02:56.056
What the hell
is wrong with you?

02:56.058 --> 02:57.291
Me? You're the one
that looks

02:57.293 --> 02:58.492
like you're
burying a dead body.

02:58.494 --> 03:00.994
It is 6:00 in the morning.

03:00.996 --> 03:02.663
I come in here
to shred in peace,

03:02.665 --> 03:04.698
and you walk in and you scare
the crap out of me.

03:04.700 --> 03:07.067
I'm sorry...
"Shred in peace"?

03:07.069 --> 03:10.070
Do you have any idea
how dangerous this machine is?

03:10.072 --> 03:11.705
Okay, I'm sorry.

03:11.707 --> 03:13.440
If you want, I can help.

03:13.442 --> 03:14.875
I'm actually here
to do some shredding myself.

03:14.877 --> 03:16.610
You know what?
Never mind.

03:16.612 --> 03:19.746
You've ruined
the whole thing.

03:19.748 --> 03:21.081
Well, the good news is,

03:21.083 --> 03:22.716
we don't have
a copy of that memo.

03:22.718 --> 03:23.951
I'm sorry
to rain on your parade,

03:23.953 --> 03:25.919
but the accusation here
isn't that you have it,

03:25.921 --> 03:27.688
it's that you buried it,

03:27.690 --> 03:28.989
so we should
probably move forward.

03:28.991 --> 03:30.290
To what?

03:30.292 --> 03:31.458
We need to put them
on the defensive.

03:31.460 --> 03:34.194
- No, we don't.
- Harvey.

03:34.196 --> 03:35.529
We need to get them
to drop the case.

03:35.531 --> 03:37.764
- And how would we do that?
- How would I do it?

03:37.766 --> 03:39.466
I would go to
the Randall family.

03:39.468 --> 03:41.001
They got screwed
and they want justice,

03:41.003 --> 03:42.469
but I'm not the guy
who screwed them,

03:42.471 --> 03:43.503
so we need to
convince them that I--

03:43.505 --> 03:45.105
Are you crazy?

03:45.107 --> 03:47.207
You trashed this woman's
dead husband in open court.

03:47.209 --> 03:48.642
Do you think
she gives a shit

03:48.644 --> 03:50.010
about whether or not
you buried that document?

03:50.012 --> 03:52.245
If you go there, you're not
just poking the bear,

03:52.247 --> 03:54.181
you're putting
a cattle prod up its ass.

03:54.183 --> 03:55.682
Is that
the same crack advice

03:55.684 --> 03:57.985
you gave Brockton Cosmetics
and Drake Consulting

03:57.987 --> 03:59.286
and Nappi LLC.?

03:59.288 --> 04:00.887
'Cause none of those companies
exist anymore.

04:00.889 --> 04:02.556
Congratulations, Harvey.

04:02.558 --> 04:05.092
You found the three cases
that I've lost in 14 years.

04:05.094 --> 04:07.027
And do you know what else
those cases have in common?

04:07.029 --> 04:10.430
Nothing. Because I learn
from my mistakes.

04:10.432 --> 04:11.798
Well, I'd prefer
to be represented by someone

04:11.800 --> 04:13.467
who doesn't make any mistakes
in the first place.

04:13.469 --> 04:15.202
Like you?

04:15.204 --> 04:16.937
Because you've been accused
of burying evidence

04:16.939 --> 04:18.605
not once, but twice.

04:18.607 --> 04:20.507
Those accusations
are bullshit.

04:20.509 --> 04:22.041
And that is
what I'm here to prove.

04:22.043 --> 04:25.579
Jessica, if I may?

04:25.581 --> 04:28.215
I don't think Harvey's problem
is with Allison.

04:28.217 --> 04:30.817
I think his problem
is with me.

04:30.819 --> 04:32.753
Daniel, we don't need
to air our laundry in here.

04:32.755 --> 04:35.155
This is
a privileged conversation.

04:35.157 --> 04:38.158
Jessica, I'm asking
you and Harvey to trust me.

04:38.160 --> 04:40.894
So I'm going to
do the same for you.

04:40.896 --> 04:45.165
I brought Allison in here
because I think she's the best.

04:45.167 --> 04:47.034
Use her or don't.

04:47.036 --> 04:51.104
But, if not, I suggest
you find someone just as good.

04:51.106 --> 04:53.507
Harvey...

04:53.509 --> 04:58.045
will you give
Allison and me a minute?

04:58.047 --> 05:01.081
Let her down easy.

05:03.284 --> 05:06.753
Allison,
I am impressed by you.

05:06.755 --> 05:08.021
But if I'm going
to give you this job,

05:08.023 --> 05:10.023
I need to know
that I can trust you.

05:10.025 --> 05:11.725
I'm a straight shooter,
Jessica.

05:11.727 --> 05:14.728
Easy to say,
harder to prove.

05:14.730 --> 05:16.296
All right,
how about this?

05:16.298 --> 05:19.232
Um, you are
an elegant woman,

05:19.234 --> 05:20.767
but there's no
getting around it...

05:20.769 --> 05:24.838
that dress does not
belong in this office.

05:27.443 --> 05:28.709
I like you.

05:28.711 --> 05:30.711
This may be something
that you don't like.

05:30.713 --> 05:33.647
You won't be the one
dictating terms here. I will.

05:33.649 --> 05:35.148
And regarding your laundry,

05:35.150 --> 05:36.917
you have my word that Danny
won't be involved,

05:36.919 --> 05:39.519
but you need to keep
that man on a leash.

05:39.521 --> 05:40.921
- She said that to your face?
- Yep.

05:40.923 --> 05:42.856
- You kick her ass out?
- Hired her on the spot.

05:42.858 --> 05:43.957
The woman insults you,

05:43.959 --> 05:45.926
all of a sudden
you're in bed with her?

05:45.928 --> 05:47.661
Maybe I should tell you
how much I hate those shoes.

05:47.663 --> 05:48.762
That's the joke
you're gonna make?

05:48.764 --> 05:50.163
What?
It's both respectful

05:50.165 --> 05:51.965
and disrespectful
at the same time.

05:51.967 --> 05:53.734
Harvey, I don't
want you to overlook

05:53.736 --> 05:56.470
the point of the story.
It's Allison's case.

05:56.472 --> 05:57.771
The firm is the client,
and you're--

05:57.773 --> 06:02.209
- The dog on a leash?
- Stay out of her way.

06:07.148 --> 06:08.415
I got the address.

06:08.417 --> 06:09.716
Then I guess it's time

06:09.718 --> 06:12.652
for this dog
to go chase some cars.

06:12.654 --> 06:16.356
♪ See the money,
wanna stay for your meal ♪

06:16.358 --> 06:19.693
♪ get another piece of pie
for your wife ♪

06:19.695 --> 06:22.863
♪ everybody wanna know
how it feel ♪

06:22.865 --> 06:26.566
♪ everybody wanna see
what it's like ♪

06:26.568 --> 06:29.503
♪ living in a beehive
of your mind ♪

06:29.505 --> 06:33.540
♪ me and missus
so busy, busy making money ♪

06:33.542 --> 06:35.008
♪ all right

06:35.010 --> 06:40.514
♪ all that time
imagine this ♪

06:40.516 --> 06:42.039
♪ the greenback boogie

